## Understanding Functional Components: The Building Blocks of React

Think of them as independent, reusable pieces of UI

Instead of writing one massive HTML file, you break your user interface down into smaller, manageable parts

This approach makes your code easier to understand,

*What are Functional Components?*

A functional component is essentially a JavaScript function that accepts an optional single argument (the props object) and returns a React element.

structure of a functional component:goto dir:  examples/module3/functionalComponent

How to Implement Functional Components : 

Step 1: Create a new file for your component:

src/components
Let's create a file named Greeting.js


Step 2: Define the functional component:

import React from 'react'; // Import React (necessary for JSX)

function Greeting(props) {
  return (
    <div>
      <h1>Hello, {props.name}!</h1>
      <p>Welcome to our application.</p>
    </div>
  );
}

export default Greeting;


